utput (str): Path for output file or '-' for standard output.\n    api_token (Optional[str]): API token for authenticating requests. Defaults to the value in the OPENROUTER_API_KEY environment variable.\n\nExample:\n    ./tool.py -i \"Translate to Spanish\" --input \"data.txt\" -m \"text-davinci\" -o result.txt --api-token \"your_api_key\"\n\nRaises:\n    SystemExit: Exits the program if an error occurs during execution, such as missing API token or output file writing errors."]}], "variables": [{"name": "llm4shell.llm.API_KEY_ENV_VAR", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "llm4shell", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "llm4shell.username", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "llm4shell.filename", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "llm4shell.litellm.openrouter_key", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "llm4shell.check_click", "xref": {"fqname": "llm4shell.utils.check_click", "project": null}}, {"name": "llm4shell.Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": null}}]}]}